      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in 90s JDM engineering. This example features the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, maintaining exceptional factory-spec compression across all rotor faces. The complex vacuum-controlled boost architecture functions flawlessly, providing a linear power band through the 5-speed short-throw manual transmission. The chassis is anchored by its original lightweight double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring surgical handling precision. Completely stock with a pristine undercarriage and an immaculate interior, this vehicle remains a benchmark of power-to-weight optimization and thermal efficiency for the discerning enthusiast.",
